Pilates is a Python library to create data for Accounting, Finance, and Economic Research.

It is able to process financial and accounting data from WRDS and other useful sources.

The library is flexible by using separate modules (plugins) to process each data
sources, such as Compustat, CRSP, IBES, FRED, etc.

To install, just run
python setup.py install

To install in develop mode (editable), run
python setup.py develop
